    {
        "user": "U02E4DAQGSZ",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1763992541.624729",
        "client_msg_id": "7cbde3eb-6a2a-40f5-bdc3-3054dea99e27",
        "text": "yeah I think of a data viz as a projection of some information `system -&gt; pixels`. If you want to go the other way `system &lt;- pixels` its a bijection which is reasonable but quite a bit more complicated to develop, so only going one is 20% of the effort for 80% of the gain (i.e. legibility). I did experiment with formalizing directly manipulatable dataviz here <https:\/\/observablehq.com\/@tomlarkworthy\/manipulate>, which shows promise.",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "27dffd0e73bd",
